text:
Thinking about taking apart breya combo factory and turning it into korvold artifacts/eggs/treasure horde. Thoughts? 
Is korvold more annoying than breya? Is an artifact build unique enough to make korvold interesting? I’m on the fence.
I think all of that is entirely both personally and meta subjective.
There's roughly 925 legal EDH commanders, and I'd probably have to have 900 or so built already before I'd even look at Korvold or Breya, but that's me.
I mean...neither of them are particularly...challenging.
Which is fine. I get the argument that people just wanna sit down and play
True enough.
hey, my breya is fun
I have a friend from high school that builds his own guitars, and I don't hold it against anyone who doesn't :slightly_smiling_face:
and has a new goal
I said nothing about fun, <@U3RJ9VDRT>

“Less annoying” is probably relative <@UDAPNDK8S> depending on what your deck actually does with it.

I like the treasure idea more than general sacrifice value.
though as soon as there is a jeskai artifact commander I'll be switching over most likely
I have a former co-worker who builds his own analog tube guitar amps, <@U4V5EHQ2G>.
I think henry's friend is cooler
I think both are gonna have the problem where your opponents spend a lot of time fucking around on their phones where you fiddle around with cardboard rectangles.

<@UA32MJW5V> had an idea for Devour-tribal. Any time you get a moderately “good-stuff” commander, theme becomes a more important aspect to make it feel unique/ not bland.

<@UDAPNDK8S> I think as long as you have a clear theme and stick with that it can be interesting.

I made my Chainer deck have a theft subtheme so it wasn’t just the most efficient creatures I could recast, and it is an absolute blast to play.

Yeah I don’t even play my breya deck, it’s a goldfish deck. I guess I’m looking at baseline stigma status of each. I don’t know that korvold necessarily has that yet but it’s very generic. 
The game plan is KCI shenanigans in jund rather than breya.
If he doesn’t yet, it’ll only be a matter of time.
ah shit, I just remembered I came up with an inifinite combo as I was falling asleep a couple of nights ago and the only thing I remember was KCI and breya

text: Sorry, I'm just now listening to your Eldraine set review.

I still think it’s pretty dull there. Repeating it is cute but it still doesn’t blow me away. That’s a lot of work to save one mana on a Diabolic Tutor that requires your commander in play to not backfire on you.
It’s also one narrow interaction compared to the whole format it’s competing against. Or the times aminatou isn’t online and you feel silly
I get the point, but I personally am all about cute.
That and...
Ah, never mind. I thought you said Demonic Tutor, not Diabolic.
That's true, but in my meta, Aminatou's not dilation a lot of hate, plus she's cheap to start with.
Also, I never feel silly!
